        "# This cell is for CODE (numbers, a query, a check).\n",
        "# Decide which pages should enter the content refresh queue first.\n",
        "# Unit of Analysis: One content page (one row per content item after preprocessing).\n",
        "# Output: A ranked list of pages with:\n",
        "#         Refresh priority score\n",
        "#         Confidence level\n",
        "#         Reason codes explaining the recommendation\n",
        "\n",
        "# Action: A content manager reviews the highest-ranked pages first and decides whether to:\n",
        "#         refresh content,\n",
        "#         improve metadata,\n",
        "#         expand content,\n",
        "#         monitor performance,\n",
        "#         or leave the page unchanged.\n",
        "\n",
        "# Cost of a Wrong Recommendation:False positives waste editorial time reviewing pages that do not need attention.\n",
        "#         False negatives leave valuable pages untreated, potentially allowing further loss in visibility or traffic.\n",
